Use Case Diagram

Shows use cases, actors, and their interrelationships. A use case is an objective users
wants to achieve with a system. 

Use case diagram provides a graphical overview of goals (represented by use cases) 
users (represented by actors) want to achieve by using the 
system (represented by system boundary but is often opt out in diagram). 
Use cases in a use case diagram can be organized and arranged according 
to their relevance, level of abstraction and impacts to users. They can be connected 
to show their dependency, inclusion and extension relationships.

